**Modify** means to change the software, in source code or compiled form.
**Modified software** means the software in source code or compiled form
that has been changed.

**Software** means the software made available under these terms.

**You** means the individual or entity exercising the license granted
under these terms.

**Your company** means any legal entity, sole proprietorship, or other
kind of organization that you work for, plus any organizations that have
control over, are under the control of, or are under common control with
that organization. **Control** means ownership of substantially all the
assets of an entity, or the power to direct its management and policies by
contract, voting, or otherwise. Control can be direct or indirect.

**Your licenses** means all the licenses granted to you for the software
under these terms.

**Use** means anything you do with the software requiring one of your
licenses.

**Commercial Uses** means uses primarily intended for or directed towards
commercial advantage or monetary compensation, including use within or for
